Package picross

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • picross.Model
  • public class Model
extends java.lang.Object
    Model Class contains the variables behind the working of the game. Contain methods for manipulating the int[][] and labels associated with gameplay.
    Author:
    Thomas Stanley

    • Method Detail

      • mapGrid

        int[][] mapGrid​(boolean isDesigned,
                boolean isRand,
                int[][] designGrid,
                int[][] defaultGrid)
        Method called when the play grid needs to be defined. If called with no design, a default grid is used. If called after grid is designed, the designed grid is returned. If called for random play, the grid elements are randomised
        Parameters:
        isDesigned - Boolean value passed to indicate if the grid has been designed or not
        isRand - Boolean value to indicated if 'random' has been selected
        designGrid - designGrid passed, this grid is used if designed beforehand
        defaultGrid - returned for both play grid and random grid modes.
        Returns:
        grid returned by method
